  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/93",
  "title": "[slider] make tooltips contenteditable",
  "body": "Something like this would be fun (@bobylito idea):\n\n![untitled screencast 5](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/9878898/474f5390-5bc5-11e5-84f6-351f0f247d22.gif)\n\nIn order to do so, [algolia/noUiSlider](https://github.com/algolia/noUiSlider) must first be enhanced to provide this new option:\n\n``` js\ntooltips: {\n  format: function() {},\n  editable: true\n}\n```\n\nThen:\n- we would have to parse the formatted tooltip in search for the numeric value\n- isolate the numeric value inside a `<span contenteditable=\"true\"></span>`\n- allow clicking the tooltip (currently it's e.preventDefault). We need to isolate drags from clicks (mousedown/touch + move = drag, mousedown/touch + mouseup/touch = click)\n- listen for contenteditable changes, update the slider and refinement accordingly\n- automatically reformat tooltip value after 100ms with no keystroke\n\nAnnnnd a lot of other possible issues to fix. But still a good idea to provide a good slider\n",
  "created_at": "2015-09-15T14:21:18Z",
